main.name: Ayda Negash
main.description: I am a junior full-stack developer.
main.bio: I am an Ethiopian born, Dallas native, and an enthusiatic student-of-life. I am currently a student with SMU for a full-stack web development program. The program includes, but is not limited to, html, css, javascript, jquery, node.js, and react.js. I am also a BJJ student under Professor Vinicius at Gracie Gym Richardson. Within the next 10 years, I plan on recieving my black belt in BJJ. I also dable in gardening. I intern at Dallas Master Gardner and volunteer in a variety of the beautiful gardens we have her in DFW. Prior to the SMU program, I was teaching Environmental Science and Art at a Wallas Foundation Funded research site in partnership with the non-profit Big Thought. In the coming future I hope to become a Master black-belt coding gardner.
